Windows:
- Install RubyInstaller from: http://railsinstaller.org/en
Then in cmd: gem install rails -v 4.2.3
- Install phantomjs from: http://phantomjs.org/download.html
... And add it to path
- Install sublime text editor
- Test installation, in cmd: rails new test_install
... And when it's all done: rails server

Linux:
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-ruby-on-rails-with-rbenv-on-ubuntu-14-04
- sudo apt-get install git-core curl zlib1g-dev build-essential libssl-dev libreadline-dev libyaml-dev libsqlite3-dev sqlite3 libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev libcurl4-openssl-dev python-software-properties libffi-dev
- sudo apt get install git gitk git-gui
- sudo apt-get install gcc build-essential libpq-dev libssl-dev libreadline-dev libsqlite3-dev zlib1g-dev
- git clone git://github.com/sstephenson/rbenv.git
  or https://github.com/sstephenson/rbenv.git
- export PATH=$PATH:/home/dragosh/utils/rbenv/bin:$PATH
- echo 'eval "$(rbenv init -)"' >> ~/.bashrc
- git clone git://github.com/sstephenson/ruby-build.git ~/utils/rbenv/plugins/ruby-build
- export PATH=$PATH:/home/dragosh/utils/rbenv/plugins/ruby-build/bin
- rbenv-install -v 2.2.2
- rbenv global 2.2.2
- Don't get documentation for gems
  echo "gem: --no-document" > ~/.gemrc
- gem install bundler
- gem install rails -v 4.2.3
- rbenv rehash
- sudo apt-get install software-properties-common python-software-properties
- sudo add-apt-repository ppa:chris-lea/node.js (?)
- sudo apt-get install nodejs
- sudo apt-get install bzip2
- export PHANTOM_JS="phantomjs-1.9.8-linux-x86_64"
  Download it from: https://bitbucket.org/ariya/phantomjs/downloads/
  And extract ...
  Or even better: download 2.0.0 source and compile!

  sudo mv $PHANTOM_JS /usr/local/share
  sudo ln -sf /usr/local/share/$PHANTOM_JS/bin/phantomjs /usr/local/bin

- Download sublime text ...

